HEADWORD: Oilman
<hw>Oil"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Oilmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who deals
in oils; formerly, one who dealt in oils and pickles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person working in the petroleum industry, esp. an
oil company executive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oilnut</ent>⟦br⟧
